      "writtenOn": "2026-06-17T16:41:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks — went EID-primary, per your point that EID is the identifier. monitor_added() and the initial sweep no longer skip endpoints that lack a UUID: we key on EID and record the UUID best-effort (empty when mctpd hasn\u0027t published it). That also dissolves the original race — discovery no longer depends on the UUID interface being present when the EID interface is emitted.\n\nConfirmed it\u0027s safe downstream: the UUID in MctpResponderInfo is stored but not consumed by any production code today (only tests reference it), and responders are keyed by object_path, so an empty UUID can\u0027t affect identification or dedup. If a later layer needs UUID it can require it there.",
      "parentUuid": "78ba6deb_52f9d79f",
      "revId": "f7a4f73b1ad8b177ffd4ab4f69a03cafc57067f4",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
